Fans of Chiranjeevi are organising blood donation camps on a regular basis to mark the birthdays of the megastar as well as those of his family members, including Pawan Kalyan, Ram Charan and Allu Arjun. Going a step further, they are gearing up to organise the biggest blood donation drive ever in the world on March 27, coinciding with Ram Charan’s birthday. All India Megastar Chiranjeevi Fans Association president Swamy Naidu said the association had tied up with agencies within the country and abroad to collect at least 1,11,116 units of blood on that day to enter the Guinness Book of Records .“We are on the job of mobilising least 10,000 volunteers from Prakasam district for the great cause,” said Prakasam district Chiranjeevi Fans Association president Chalapati Ram Babu and Pawan Kalyan Seva Dal president Bujji.